Edition: 1961
Quote: Hence, a swindler, as in `Speeler...One who gets his living by Gambling or Swindling', W. Newton, Secrets of Tramp Life Revealed, 1886; July 14, 1898, The Daily Telegraph, where it is classified as `Australian'; 1909, Ware; 1925, Leverage, `A stall; the engager [of others] in a crooked game'; July 13, 1929, Flynne's; 1933, Ersine; 1936, P.S. Van Cise, Fighting the Underworld, `Second inside man, or mysterious stramger' in a `con mob'; 1942, Baker (Australia), `A swind- ler, a welsher, a card-sharp'; extant.
