Vol / Page: 2031
Edition:
Quote: <i>Spiel&#769;.er </i>(sp&emacr.l&#769;.&etilde.r), n. (Ger. <i>spieler </i> player, gamester, fr. Ger. <i>spielen </i> to play, to gamble, which is akin to AS <i>. spilian </i> to play.] One who makes a practice at derfrauding others by cheating at play; a professional sharper. <i>[Colloq.] </i>
